  "body": "# Allow user to format selected text through non-native composer\r\n\r\n| As a user\r\n\r\n| I want to be able to style selected text through the non-native composer\r\n\r\n| So I don’t have to learn markdown\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWhen selecting text, if the user clicks on the non-native text formatting composer, it should wrap the selected text with the relevant markdown.\r\n\r\nFor example, if the user has written “blah” in the input box, if they click on `Aa` followed by `B`\r\n\r\nit should wrap “blah” in the bold formatting, resulting in `**blah**`\r\n\r\n### Designs\r\n\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/wA8Epdki2OWa8Vr067PCNQ/Composer-for-Mobile?node-id=2630%3A207636\r\n\r\nDepennds on: https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/issues/14136",
